Apograph — unofficial PoliTo Bachelor/Master thesis
===================================================

This project is not an official Politecnico di Torino template and is not
endorsed by Politecnico di Torino. Institution names and marks belong to their
respective owners.

Upstream template
-----------------

This starter is adapted from:

  Luigi De Russis, “Politecnico di Torino Thesis Template”
  https://www.overleaf.com/latex/templates/politecnico-di-torino-thesis-template/cmpmxftwvvbr
  Overleaf project description: Creative Commons CC BY 4.0
  Local reference snapshot reviewed 2026-07-18

The upstream project describes itself as a template for both Master's and
Bachelor's theses, built on the maintained toptesi class and aligned with
published PoliTo thesis guidance and the 2023 Visual Identity Manual.

Apograph modifications
----------------------

Elia Innocenti adapted and repackaged the source in 2026. Changes include:

- one configuration switch for Bachelor's or Master's toptesi mode;
- a small config/main/content/theme project structure that consolidates the
  upstream common files without redesigning the document;
- extensible candidate and supervisor rows plus an optional co-supervisor
  block;
- preservation of the upstream Latin Modern typography, title-page geometry,
  package feature set, document flow, and teaching content;
- a compiling, same-footprint text fallback for the absent institution logo;
- self-contained Apograph artifacts with root-vendored shared modules.

The adapted thesis files are distributed under CC-BY-4.0. The complete text is
in LICENSES/CC-BY-4.0.txt. Apograph shared modules vendored into an artifact are
separate MIT-licensed components covered by the repository root license and
their file headers.

Published guidance
------------------

The implementation was compared on 2026-07-18 with PoliTo's published thesis
guidance (“Writing your thesis”) and the cited “Saper Comunicare” and 2023
Visual Identity Manual references. Those sources are requirements/design
evidence only: they do not make this adaptation official or endorsed.

Institution asset
-----------------

The PoliTo logo is not included. It is cataloged as an optional user-provided
file at theme/assets/polito-logo.jpg. To reproduce the upstream title page, the
expected source is its horizontal blue 2021 JPEG logo (the upstream reference
file is named polito_logo_2021_blu-2-2.jpg). PoliTo's student guidance says
enrolled users can obtain the title-page template and logo from the private
Teaching Portal and may use the logo for academic purposes. The public
corporate-image policy separately states that third-party logo use requires
authorization.
Supplying a file locally does not imply permission to redistribute or use it in
another context.
